hopobject.body: I've got a very weak signal preo do xytomax e ultra edge xl Meteor showers result from the trails left behind by comets. Whenever a comet loops around the sun, it loses gas and solid particles, leaving behind a breadcrumb trail of dust grains. The comet responsible for the Draconids,Â Giacobini-Zinner, spins past the sun every 6.6 years, so it has traced and re-traced its path through the solar system. When Earth's orbit crosses these overlapping trails of cometary crumbs, the dust grains get caught by Earth's gravity and fall toward the surface, glowing brightly as they burn up in our atmosphere. That flaming destruction creates the brilliant path that the ancients called shooting stars, and which scientists call meteors.
